  (428, 'david-dirkman-the-friday-night-turbo-champion', 'David Dirkman, the  Friday Night Turbo Champion! 🏆', 'Congratulations to David Dirkman, your Friday Night Turbo Champion! 🏆 The final three players agreed to a modified chop and played it out for the win and points, great finish all around! 36 players and 49 add-ons built a $6,800 prize pool 💰…', '2026-04-18 01:21:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-04-17-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6747-PHKeh3iO.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6747-PHKeh3iO.jpg', null, '{"id":428,"title":"David Dirkman, the  Friday Night Turbo Champion! 🏆","alias":"david-dirkman-the-friday-night-turbo-champion","excerpt":"Congratulations to David Dirkman, your Friday Night Turbo Champion! 🏆 The final three players agreed to a modified chop and played it out for the win and points, great finish all around! 36 players and 49 add-ons built a $6,800 prize pool 💰…","content":"Congratulations to David Dirkman, your Friday Night Turbo Champion! 🏆 The final three players agreed to a modified chop and played it out for the win and points, great finish all around! 36 players and 49 add-ons built a $6,800 prize pool 💰 Results: 1st – $1,760 David Dirkman (Dalton, MN) 2nd – $1,760 Michael Driscoll (Lake Park, MN) 3rd – $1,760 Christian Young (West Fargo, ND) 4th – $880 Wade Kyser (Erie, ND) 5th – $620 Chase Lardy (Fargo, ND) Thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and the Casselton Vets Club. We appreciate you all! Don’t miss tomorrow’s action ⬇️ 🍝 SATURDAY DINNER BREAK SPECIAL 🍝 Spaghetti, bread, and side salad for just $8 (gluten-free available) 🇺🇸 Vets eat FREE – thank you for your service! 🏆 SATURDAY SINGLE DAY EVENT – 4/18/2026 🏆 Registration: 11:00 AM Cards in the Air: 12:00 NOON $150 buy-in – 20,000 chips 30-minute levels $50 add-ons for 10K (up to 3x, max $300) Add-ons anytime, including at the start & for re-entry Late reg/re-entry open through dinner break (~5 PM) $20 suggested dealer appreciation – optional but appreciated Who’s coming back for Day 2? ♠️♦️♣️♥️","publishedAt":"2026-04-18 01:21:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_6747-PHKeh3iO.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6747-PHKeh3iO.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":341,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-04-17-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (427, 'casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-underway', 'Casselton Vets Friday Night Turbo Underway', 'Cards are in the air at the Casselton Vets Club! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ We’ve got 4 tables going strong and growing, late registration is open until 8:15 PM, so there’s still time to get in the action! Friday Night Turbo – 4/17/2026 Registration opened a…', '2026-04-17 19:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-04-17-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/674434535_1626215662838839_3101149415253439377_n-OjBpK678.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/674434535_1626215662838839_3101149415253439377_n-OjBpK678.jpg', null, '{"id":427,"title":"Casselton Vets Friday Night Turbo Underway","alias":"casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-underway","excerpt":"Cards are in the air at the Casselton Vets Club! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ We’ve got 4 tables going strong and growing, late registration is open until 8:15 PM, so there’s still time to get in the action! Friday Night Turbo – 4/17/2026 Registration opened a…","content":"Cards are in the air at the Casselton Vets Club! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ We’ve got 4 tables going strong and growing, late registration is open until 8:15 PM, so there’s still time to get in the action! Friday Night Turbo – 4/17/2026 Registration opened at 5 PM Cards in the air at 6 PM 20-minute blinds $100 re-buys for 15K chips $100 add-on for 15K chips at close of registration Max buy-in $300 Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips are appreciated but not mandatory to play) Come out, jump in, and chase it down 🔥 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-04-17 19:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"674434535_1626215662838839_3101149415253439377_n-OjBpK678.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/674434535_1626215662838839_3101149415253439377_n-OjBpK678.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":341,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-casselton-vets-friday-night-turbo-04-17-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (426, 'john-wendlick-of-dickinson-nd-is-the-buckskin-shootout-champion', 'John Wendlick of Dickinson, ND Is the Buckskin Shootout Champion', 'Congratulations to our Buckskin Shootout Deep Stack Champion! 🏆 John Wendlick of Dickinson, ND battled through a tough field of 56 players to take down the title and $4,200 in cash! What a run! Here’s a look at our final table payouts: 1st…', '2026-03-29 03:46:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6234-2Eo9Tr2Y.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6234-2Eo9Tr2Y.jpg', null, '{"id":426,"title":"John Wendlick of Dickinson, ND Is the Buckskin Shootout Champion","alias":"john-wendlick-of-dickinson-nd-is-the-buckskin-shootout-champion","excerpt":"Congratulations to our Buckskin Shootout Deep Stack Champion! 🏆 John Wendlick of Dickinson, ND battled through a tough field of 56 players to take down the title and $4,200 in cash! What a run! Here’s a look at our final table payouts: 1st…","content":"Congratulations to our Buckskin Shootout Deep Stack Champion! 🏆 John Wendlick of Dickinson, ND battled through a tough field of 56 players to take down the title and $4,200 in cash! What a run! Here’s a look at our final table payouts: 1st – $4,200 John Wendlick (Dickinson, ND) 2nd – $2,700 Kelly Allmendinger (Dodge, ND) 3rd – $2,000 Placido Sotelo (Dunn Center, ND) 4th – $1,400 Lester Hauglid (Detroit Lakes, MN) 5th – $1,150 James Lonenz (Dunn Center, ND) 6th – $950 Niles Short (Minnewaukan, ND) 7th – $800 Andrew Dertinger (New York Mills, MN) 8th – $600 Bryce Shypkoski (Dickinson, ND) 9th – $465 Jeff Parker (Dickinson, ND) Thank you to all the players who came out and made this event such a great success, we appreciate the continued support of the Dakota Poker Tour! A huge thank you to our host venue, the Buckskin Saloon, for the hospitality, and to our incredible charity partner, Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, for everything they do, taking only the state minimum 10% and giving the maximum back to the players. We also want to give a special shoutout to our amazing dealers. These events simply don’t happen without you. Your time, energy, and professionalism are what keep everything running smoothly. And thank you to First International Bank & Trust for your support and helping take care of the players throughout the event. They provided (2) drinks of choice to every player and lunch! Another great stop in the books—who’s ready for the next one? ♠️♦️♣️♥️ DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT Youtube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-29 03:46:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_6234-2Eo9Tr2Y.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6234-2Eo9Tr2Y.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":340,"name":"Buckskin Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (425, '56-players-14k-prize-pool-who-s-taking-home-4-200-tonight', '56 Players, $14K Prize Pool – Who’s Taking Home $4,200 Tonight? 💰', 'Registration is officially CLOSED tonight with 56 players in the field, generating an impressive $14,265 prize pool! 💰 One of these players will walk away with $4,200 in CASH—who’s it going to be?! Huge thank you to everyone who came out to…', '2026-03-28 21:38:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6226-eNB73PxB.png', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6226-eNB73PxB.png', null, '{"id":425,"title":"56 Players, $14K Prize Pool – Who’s Taking Home $4,200 Tonight? 💰","alias":"56-players-14k-prize-pool-who-s-taking-home-4-200-tonight","excerpt":"Registration is officially CLOSED tonight with 56 players in the field, generating an impressive $14,265 prize pool! 💰 One of these players will walk away with $4,200 in CASH—who’s it going to be?! Huge thank you to everyone who came out to…","content":"Registration is officially CLOSED tonight with 56 players in the field, generating an impressive $14,265 prize pool! 💰 One of these players will walk away with $4,200 in CASH—who’s it going to be?! Huge thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour, our charity partner Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, and our host venue Buckskin Saloon. And a special shoutout to 1st International Bank & Trust for going above and beyond—providing food and TWO drinks of choice for all players today. We appreciate the support! Let’s play it down and see who takes it home! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT Youtube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-28 21:38:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_6226-eNB73PxB.png","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6226-eNB73PxB.png","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":340,"name":"Buckskin Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (424, 'cards-are-in-the-air-in-killdeer-nd-and-it-s-a-full-house', 'Cards are in the air in Killdeer, ND and it’s a FULL HOUSE', 'Cards are in the air in Killdeer, ND and it’s a FULL HOUSE to kick things off! 🔥 We’re rolling with 6 tables to start and plenty of room to grow,so there’s still time to get in on the action. Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons are ope…', '2026-03-28 14:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6174-G3LruVoq.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6174-G3LruVoq.jpg', null, '{"id":424,"title":"Cards are in the air in Killdeer, ND and it’s a FULL HOUSE","alias":"cards-are-in-the-air-in-killdeer-nd-and-it-s-a-full-house","excerpt":"Cards are in the air in Killdeer, ND and it’s a FULL HOUSE to kick things off! 🔥 We’re rolling with 6 tables to start and plenty of room to grow,so there’s still time to get in on the action. Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons are ope…","content":"Cards are in the air in Killdeer, ND and it’s a FULL HOUSE to kick things off! 🔥 We’re rolling with 6 tables to start and plenty of room to grow,so there’s still time to get in on the action. Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons are open until the dinner break at approximately 5 PM MT! The Prize Pool is already over $10,000! Last year’s Deep Stack champion, Merrill Pearcy, took home $4,600… who’s making a run at it this year? 💰 As always, thank you to our charity partner, Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, who will once again be taking the state minimum 10%, giving the maximum back to the players. Tournament Details: $150 buy-in for 20,000 chips 30-minute levels $50 add-on for 10,000 chips (up to 3 times, max buy-in $300) Add-ons available anytime—including at the start—and can be used for re-entry Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons open until ~5 PM (dinner break) Suggested dealer appreciation $20 – tips appreciated, not required Still time to get here—don’t miss your shot! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ Who’s making the trip to Killdeer this weekend? DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-28 14:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_6174-G3LruVoq.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6174-G3LruVoq.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":340,"name":"Buckskin Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (423, 'who-s-ready-for-the-buckskin-shootout-deep-stack', 'Who’s ready for the Buckskin Shootout Deep Stack?! ♠️', 'Today’s the day, Killdeer! Saturday, March 28, 2026 Registration opens at 11 AM Cards in the air at NOON (MT) Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons remain open through the dinner break (approximately 5 PM), so there’s still plenty of tim…', '2026-03-28 11:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6158-NRM7j39V.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6158-NRM7j39V.jpg', null, '{"id":423,"title":"Who’s ready for the Buckskin Shootout Deep Stack?! ♠️","alias":"who-s-ready-for-the-buckskin-shootout-deep-stack","excerpt":"Today’s the day, Killdeer! Saturday, March 28, 2026 Registration opens at 11 AM Cards in the air at NOON (MT) Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons remain open through the dinner break (approximately 5 PM), so there’s still plenty of tim…","content":"Today’s the day, Killdeer! Saturday, March 28, 2026 Registration opens at 11 AM Cards in the air at NOON (MT) Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons remain open through the dinner break (approximately 5 PM), so there’s still plenty of time to get in the action! Last year’s Deep Stack champion, Merrill Pearcy, took home $4,600… who’s taking it down this year? $150 buy-in – 20,000 starting chips 30-minute levels $50 add-on for 10,000 chips (up to 3 times) Max buy-in: $300 Add-ons can be taken at any time and used for re-entry Come out and support the Dakota Poker Tour, our host venue the Buckskin Saloon , and our charity partner Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, who once again will be taking the state minimum 10%, giving the maximum back to the players. Suggested dealer appreciation: $20 (tips appreciated but not required) Let’s pack the room, build a big prize pool, and crown a new champion today! 💰🏆 Who’s making the trip to Killdeer this weekend? ♠️♦️♣️♥️","publishedAt":"2026-03-28 11:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_6158-NRM7j39V.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6158-NRM7j39V.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":340,"name":"Buckskin Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-deep-stack-03-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (422, 'buckskin-shootout-friday-night-turbo-champion-crowned', 'Buckskin Shootout Friday Night Turbo Champion Crowned! ♠️♦️♣️♥️', 'Congratulations to Ryan Bickhart of Watford City, ND on taking down the Buckskin Shootout Friday Night Turbo and cashing in $2,700! 💰 A total of 40 players hit the felt tonight, building an impressive $8,500 prize pool and bringing the ener…', '2026-03-28 01:15:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6164-ihKzHgXA.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6164-ihKzHgXA.jpg', null, '{"id":422,"title":"Buckskin Shootout Friday Night Turbo Champion Crowned! ♠️♦️♣️♥️","alias":"buckskin-shootout-friday-night-turbo-champion-crowned","excerpt":"Congratulations to Ryan Bickhart of Watford City, ND on taking down the Buckskin Shootout Friday Night Turbo and cashing in $2,700! 💰 A total of 40 players hit the felt tonight, building an impressive $8,500 prize pool and bringing the ener…","content":"Congratulations to Ryan Bickhart of Watford City, ND on taking down the Buckskin Shootout Friday Night Turbo and cashing in $2,700! 💰 A total of 40 players hit the felt tonight, building an impressive $8,500 prize pool and bringing the energy to the Buckskin Saloon! Full Results: 1st – $2,700 Ryan Bickhart – Watford City, ND 2nd – $1,900 Benji Milner – Killdeer, ND 3rd – $1,400 Nanette Edmondson – Killdeer, ND 4th – $1,000 Allan Gunderson – Baker, MT 5th – $800 Mark Britton – Mapleton, ND 6th – $660 Tara Milner – Killdeer, ND Thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour, our host venue Buckskin Saloon, and our charity partner Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, who continues to take only the state minimum—putting the maximum back into the prize pool for the players. We also want to thank all of our volunteer dealers—these events wouldn’t be possible without you! We’ll see everyone back tomorrow for the Saturday Deep Stack! Saturday Deep Stack – March 28, 2026 Registration opens at 11 AM Cards in the air at NOON $150 buy-in – 20,000 chips 30-minute levels $50 add-on (10,000 chips) up to 3 times (max $300 buy-in) Add-ons available anytime and can be used for re-entry Late registration open through dinner break (approx. 5 PM) Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated, not required) Last year’s champion Merrill Pearcy took home $4,600… who’s next? 👀","publishedAt":"2026-03-28 01:15:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_6164-ihKzHgXA.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6164-ihKzHgXA.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":339,"name":"Buckskin Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (420, 'registration-closes-with-40-players-8-500-prize-pool-up-for-grabs', 'Registration Closes with 40 Players, $8,500 Prize Pool Up for Grabs', 'Registration is officially CLOSED with 40 players in the field, creating an $8,500 prize pool! 💰 One of these players is about to walk away with $2,700 CASH — not bad for a Friday night! 🔥 Thank you again to all the players who came out to…', '2026-03-27 23:42:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6156-k8Xqrb0A.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6156-k8Xqrb0A.jpg', null, '{"id":420,"title":"Registration Closes with 40 Players, $8,500 Prize Pool Up for Grabs","alias":"registration-closes-with-40-players-8-500-prize-pool-up-for-grabs","excerpt":"Registration is officially CLOSED with 40 players in the field, creating an $8,500 prize pool! 💰 One of these players is about to walk away with $2,700 CASH — not bad for a Friday night! 🔥 Thank you again to all the players who came out to…","content":"Registration is officially CLOSED with 40 players in the field, creating an $8,500 prize pool! 💰 One of these players is about to walk away with $2,700 CASH — not bad for a Friday night! 🔥 Thank you again to all the players who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour, our host venue, and our charity partner, Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, who continues to give back by taking only the state minimum. Good luck to everyone still in the hunt — let’s see who takes it down! ♠️♦️♣️♥️ DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-27 23:42:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_6156-k8Xqrb0A.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6156-k8Xqrb0A.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":339,"name":"Buckskin Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (421, 'friday-night-turbo-is-underway-with-4-tables', 'The Buckskin Friday Night Turbo is Underway', 'Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo! We’re starting strong with 4 tables and room to grow, get down here and jump in the action! Late registration is open until 8:20 PM MT, so there’s still time to grab a seat and run it up. Com…', '2026-03-27 19:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6131-kB0YK7ys.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6131-kB0YK7ys.jpg', null, '{"id":421,"title":"The Buckskin Friday Night Turbo is Underway","alias":"friday-night-turbo-is-underway-with-4-tables","excerpt":"Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo! We’re starting strong with 4 tables and room to grow, get down here and jump in the action! Late registration is open until 8:20 PM MT, so there’s still time to grab a seat and run it up. Com…","content":"Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo! We’re starting strong with 4 tables and room to grow, get down here and jump in the action! Late registration is open until 8:20 PM MT, so there’s still time to grab a seat and run it up. Come out and support the Dakota Poker Tour, our host venue Buckskin Saloon, and our charity partner, Ezra Barrows Post 46 American Legion, who is once again taking the state minimum 10%, giving the maximum back to the players. Last year’s Friday Night Turbo winner David Golombowski took home $2,200 Friday Night Turbo – Friday, March 27, 2026 Registration opened at 5 PM Cards in the air at 6 PM 20-minute blinds Late registration until 8:20 PM MT $100 buy-in for 15,000 chips $100 re-buys/add-on for 15,000 chips until close of registration Suggested dealer appreciation $20 – tips are appreciated but not mandatory to play DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-27 19:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_6131-kB0YK7ys.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6131-kB0YK7ys.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":339,"name":"Buckskin Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buckskin-shootout-buckskin-friday-night-turbo-03-27-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (419, 'shawn-cote-from-tioga-nd-is-the-pour-decisions-champion', 'Shawn Cote from Tioga ND is the Pour Decisions Champion', '♠️ Congratulations to Shawn Cote — your Pour Decisions Champion! ♠️ We had 24 players come out today for an awesome day of poker, building a prize pool of $5,830! 💰 A huge thank you to all the players for your support of the Dakota Poker To…', '2026-03-22 00:19:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-pour-decisions-deep-stack-pour-decisions-deep-stack-03-21-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6058-kvdIE62a.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_6058-kvdIE62a.jpg', null, '{"id":419,"title":"Shawn Cote from Tioga ND is the Pour Decisions Champion","alias":"shawn-cote-from-tioga-nd-is-the-pour-decisions-champion","excerpt":"♠️ Congratulations to Shawn Cote — your Pour Decisions Champion! ♠️ We had 24 players come out today for an awesome day of poker, building a prize pool of $5,830! 💰 A huge thank you to all the players for your support of the Dakota Poker To…","content":"♠️ Congratulations to Shawn Cote — your Pour Decisions Champion! ♠️ We had 24 players come out today for an awesome day of poker, building a prize pool of $5,830! 💰 A huge thank you to all the players for your support of the Dakota Poker Tour, our charity partner Prairie Public Broadcasting, and our host venue, Poor Decisions in Tioga, North Dakota. We truly appreciate each and every one of you! 🙌 🏆 Final Results: 1st – $2,100 Shawn Cote (Tioga, ND) 2nd – $1,400 Colton Parham (Powell, WY) 3rd – $1,000 Shannon Evans (Williston, ND) 4th – $800 Scott White (Dickinson, ND) 5th – $530 David Holanson (Williston, ND) We’ll see everyone next weekend in Killdeer, ND — don’t miss it! 🔗 DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 🔗 DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🔗 YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-22 00:19:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_6058-kvdIE62a.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_6058-kvdIE62a.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":338,"name":"Pour Decisions Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-pour-decisions-deep-stack-pour-decisions-deep-stack-03-21-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (418, 'tioga-nd-lets-play-poker', 'Tioga ND Lets Play Poker', '🚨 Dakota Poker Tour is headed to Tioga, North Dakota! 🚨 The DPT has officially arrived at Pour Decisions, and we’re ready to shuffle up for an action-packed Deep Stack event! Who’s ready to run deep and take it down in Tioga? 👀 ♠️♦️♣️♥️ Sat…', '2026-03-21 13:03:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-pour-decisions-deep-stack-pour-decisions-deep-stack-03-21-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/653499935_1602101801916892_6979512571715754921_n-Ce4c0voQ.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/653499935_1602101801916892_6979512571715754921_n-Ce4c0voQ.jpg', null, '{"id":418,"title":"Tioga ND Lets Play Poker","alias":"tioga-nd-lets-play-poker","excerpt":"🚨 Dakota Poker Tour is headed to Tioga, North Dakota! 🚨 The DPT has officially arrived at Pour Decisions, and we’re ready to shuffle up for an action-packed Deep Stack event! Who’s ready to run deep and take it down in Tioga? 👀 ♠️♦️♣️♥️ Sat…","content":"🚨 Dakota Poker Tour is headed to Tioga, North Dakota! 🚨 The DPT has officially arrived at Pour Decisions, and we’re ready to shuffle up for an action-packed Deep Stack event! Who’s ready to run deep and take it down in Tioga? 👀 ♠️♦️♣️♥️ Saturday Deep Stack – March 21, 2026 • Registration opens at 11 AM • Cards in the air at NOON Tournament Details: • $150 Buy-in – 20,000 starting chips • 30-minute levels • $50 Add-on for 10,000 chips (up to 3 times) • Max buy-in: $300 • Add-ons can be taken anytime (including at the start) and used for re-entry • Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons open through dinner break (~5 PM) • Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated, not required) 💥 Plenty of play, plenty of chips, and plenty of chances to build a stack! Who’s taking home the cash and bragging rights this weekend?!","publishedAt":"2026-03-21 13:03:00","featured":false,"logo":"653499935_1602101801916892_6979512571715754921_n-Ce4c0voQ.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/653499935_1602101801916892_6979512571715754921_n-Ce4c0voQ.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":338,"name":"Pour Decisions Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-pour-decisions-deep-stack-pour-decisions-deep-stack-03-21-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (417, 'kyle-mcgarry-of-glyndon-nd-our-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-champion', 'Kyle McGarry of Glyndon, ND our L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack Champion', 'Congratulations to Kyle McGarry of Glyndon, ND our L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack Champion at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Kyle outlasted a field of 77 players to take home the title, trophy, and $5,800 in CASH from a $19,640 prize pool. I…', '2026-03-15 00:37:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5960-IM0nS5IX.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5960-IM0nS5IX.jpg', null, '{"id":417,"title":"Kyle McGarry of Glyndon, ND our L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack Champion","alias":"kyle-mcgarry-of-glyndon-nd-our-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-champion","excerpt":"Congratulations to Kyle McGarry of Glyndon, ND our L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack Champion at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Kyle outlasted a field of 77 players to take home the title, trophy, and $5,800 in CASH from a $19,640 prize pool. I…","content":"Congratulations to Kyle McGarry of Glyndon, ND our L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack Champion at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Kyle outlasted a field of 77 players to take home the title, trophy, and $5,800 in CASH from a $19,640 prize pool. It was a great day of poker with players battling through deep stacks and tough competition to reach the final table. We want to give a huge thank you to all the players who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and made this another fantastic event. A special thank you to our charity partner, L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc, for working with us to make this tournament possible, and to the Canad Inn in Grand Forks for hosting us and providing a great venue for the event. Thank you to Ms. Lillie from L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc for handling registration and greeting players throughout the day with a welcoming smile. And of course, a massive thank you to all of our volunteer dealers. Your time, effort, and dedication keep these tournaments running smoothly, we truly could not do it without you. Congratulations again to Kyle McGarry, our Monster Stack Champion! 🏆♠️♦️♣️♥️ 2nd $3700 Basim Habib Moorhead MN 3rd $2740 Leslie Haagenson Leeds ND 4th $1960 Ron Miller Avon MN 5th $1600 Bruce Kulseth Thompson ND 6th $1300 Cheezin Chase Lardy Fargo ND 7th $1060 Robert Kessel Grand Forks ND 8th $840 Zach Gronsberg East Grand Forks MN 9th $650 Jeremy Johnson Grandforks ND DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-15 00:37:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5960-IM0nS5IX.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5960-IM0nS5IX.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":337,"name":"Monster Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (416, 'congratulations-to-our-final-table-at-the-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack', 'Congratulations to our final table at the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack', 'Congratulations to our final table at the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack here at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND! Out of 77 players who came out to compete, these final 9 have battled their way through the field and secured a spot at the f…', '2026-03-14 21:55:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5945-oAobcQys.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5945-oAobcQys.jpg', null, '{"id":416,"title":"Congratulations to our final table at the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack","alias":"congratulations-to-our-final-table-at-the-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack","excerpt":"Congratulations to our final table at the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack here at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND! Out of 77 players who came out to compete, these final 9 have battled their way through the field and secured a spot at the f…","content":"Congratulations to our final table at the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack here at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND! Out of 77 players who came out to compete, these final 9 have battled their way through the field and secured a spot at the final table. With a $19,640 prize pool on the line and $5,800 up top, the pressure is on as these players now fight for the Monster Stack Champion title and trophy. All nine players remaining are guaranteed a cash payout, but only one will walk away with the top prize. Best of luck to our final table as they battle it out! Let’s see who will be crowned the Dakota Poker Tour Monster Stack Champion tonight. ♠️♦️♣️♥️🏆 DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-14 21:55:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5945-oAobcQys.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5945-oAobcQys.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":337,"name":"Monster Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (415, 'monster-stack-draws-77-players-in-grand-forks', 'Monster Stack Draws 77 Players in Grand Forks', 'Thank you to everyone who came out to the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! We had an incredible turnout with 77 players, generating a prize pool of $19,640. Tonight’s champion will be taking home a sweet troph…', '2026-03-14 18:44:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5942-5GtNzNYx.png', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5942-5GtNzNYx.png', null, '{"id":415,"title":"Monster Stack Draws 77 Players in Grand Forks","alias":"monster-stack-draws-77-players-in-grand-forks","excerpt":"Thank you to everyone who came out to the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! We had an incredible turnout with 77 players, generating a prize pool of $19,640. Tonight’s champion will be taking home a sweet troph…","content":"Thank you to everyone who came out to the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! We had an incredible turnout with 77 players, generating a prize pool of $19,640. Tonight’s champion will be taking home a sweet trophy, the title of Monster Stack Champion, and $5,800 in CASH! The top 9 players will all be walking away with a payday today. We also want to send a huge thank you to all of our volunteer dealers, without you, these tournaments would not be possible. Your time and dedication help make these events run smoothly and we truly appreciate it. A special thank you to Ms Lillie at the registration desk, greeting all the players with a big smile and making everyone feel welcome as they arrived. Again, thank you to all the players who continue to support the Dakota Poker Tour, our charity partner L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc, and all the new friends we made along the way. We truly appreciate everyone who came out to make this another great event. DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-14 18:44:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5942-5GtNzNYx.png","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5942-5GtNzNYx.png","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":337,"name":"Monster Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (414, 'dakota-poker-tour-is-at-the-canad-inn-in-grand-forks-nd-for-the-monster-stack-event', 'Dakota Poker Tour is at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND for the Monster Stack event!', 'We’re off to a strong start with 7 tables running and room to grow. Late registration is open until 6 PM, so there is still plenty of time to get in on the action. Last year’s Monster Stack Champion was Sara Weishaar, who took home $6,000.…', '2026-03-14 13:33:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/651439665_1595899975870408_1131605283142510705_n-YGejH793.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/651439665_1595899975870408_1131605283142510705_n-YGejH793.jpg', null, '{"id":414,"title":"Dakota Poker Tour is at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND for the Monster Stack event!","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-is-at-the-canad-inn-in-grand-forks-nd-for-the-monster-stack-event","excerpt":"We’re off to a strong start with 7 tables running and room to grow. Late registration is open until 6 PM, so there is still plenty of time to get in on the action. Last year’s Monster Stack Champion was Sara Weishaar, who took home $6,000.…","content":"We’re off to a strong start with 7 tables running and room to grow. Late registration is open until 6 PM, so there is still plenty of time to get in on the action. Last year’s Monster Stack Champion was Sara Weishaar, who took home $6,000. Who is going to make the run this year? Saturday – L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack New Start Time: 11 AM $300 Buy-in One-Day Monster Stack Event 100,000 starting chips | 30-minutes Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated but not required) Come out, shuffle up, and see who runs deep in Grand Forks! DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour Who’s making the trip to Grand Forks this weekend?","publishedAt":"2026-03-14 13:33:00","featured":false,"logo":"651439665_1595899975870408_1131605283142510705_n-YGejH793.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/651439665_1595899975870408_1131605283142510705_n-YGejH793.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":337,"name":"Monster Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-monster-stack-03-14-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (413, 'cole', 'Cole Johnson of Grand Forks, ND Friday Night Turbo Champion', 'Congratulations to Cole Johnson of Grand Forks, North Dakota, who captured the title in the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend at the Canad Inn! In an incredible story, Cole outlasted a field of 61 players with…', '2026-03-14 01:17:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5901-hrDRsaxd.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5901-hrDRsaxd.jpg', null, '{"id":413,"title":"Cole Johnson of Grand Forks, ND Friday Night Turbo Champion","alias":"cole","excerpt":"Congratulations to Cole Johnson of Grand Forks, North Dakota, who captured the title in the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend at the Canad Inn! In an incredible story, Cole outlasted a field of 61 players with…","content":"Congratulations to Cole Johnson of Grand Forks, North Dakota, who captured the title in the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend at the Canad Inn! In an incredible story, Cole outlasted a field of 61 players with 84 rebuys/add-ons, generating a $12,150 prize pool, and took home $3,600 in cash for the victory. Even more impressive, this was Cole’s very first live poker tournament! Talk about making a debut in style. Thank you to everyone who came out to support the event and L.I.S.T.E.N. INC. We appreciate all the players who traveled to Grand Forks and made the night a huge success. We’ll see everyone back tomorrow for the Monster Stack — cards in the air at 11 AM! Who’s going to be the next champion? 2nd $2200 Rob Urbatsch Grand Forks ND 3rd $1800 Mark Britton Mapleton ND 4th $1300 Carlos Vallee Tomasini 5th $1100 Ron James West Fargo ND 6th $900 Anthony Hendricks Thief River Falls MN 7th $700 Jon Wurden Fisher MN 8th $550 Eric McPherson Shelly MN DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-14 01:17:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5901-hrDRsaxd.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5901-hrDRsaxd.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":336,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (411, 'final-table-update-friday-night-turbo-at-the-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack', 'Final Table of the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack', 'We have reached the final table here at the Friday Night Turbo at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Tonight’s event brought out a strong field of 61 players, with 84 rebuys and add-ons, generating an impressive $12,150 prize pool. Not bad for a…', '2026-03-13 23:30:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5897-aqGWix7e.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5897-aqGWix7e.jpg', null, '{"id":411,"title":"Final Table of the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack","alias":"final-table-update-friday-night-turbo-at-the-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack","excerpt":"We have reached the final table here at the Friday Night Turbo at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Tonight’s event brought out a strong field of 61 players, with 84 rebuys and add-ons, generating an impressive $12,150 prize pool. Not bad for a…","content":"We have reached the final table here at the Friday Night Turbo at the Canad Inn in Grand Forks! Tonight’s event brought out a strong field of 61 players, with 84 rebuys and add-ons, generating an impressive $12,150 prize pool. Not bad for a Friday night! First place will take home $3,600 in CASH, with the top 8 players all getting paid. Thank you to all the players who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and our charity partner, LISTEN Inc. We appreciate everyone who continues to make these events such a success. We’ll see everyone back tomorrow for the main event of the weekend: Saturday – L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack NEW START TIME: 11 AM $300 Buy-in One-Day Monster Stack Event 100,000 starting chips | 30-minute levels Late registration available until 6 PM after the dinner break Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated but not required) Last year’s Saturday Monster Stack Champion – Sara Weishaar – $6,000 Come out, shuffle up, and see who runs deep in Grand Forks! DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour Who’s coming back tomorrow to take their shot at the Monster Stack? ♠️♦️♣️♥️","publishedAt":"2026-03-13 23:30:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5897-aqGWix7e.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5897-aqGWix7e.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":336,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (410, 'cards-are-in-the-air-for-the-friday-night-turbo', 'Cards Are in the Air for the Friday Night Turbo', 'Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack at the Canad Inns in Grand Forks! We’re kicking things off strong with 5 tables already going, and there’s still plenty of time to get down here. Late reg…', '2026-03-13 19:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/651233183_1595244512602621_8432823892227840256_n-GJW9DuMV.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/651233183_1595244512602621_8432823892227840256_n-GJW9DuMV.jpg', null, '{"id":410,"title":"Cards Are in the Air for the Friday Night Turbo","alias":"cards-are-in-the-air-for-the-friday-night-turbo","excerpt":"Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack at the Canad Inns in Grand Forks! We’re kicking things off strong with 5 tables already going, and there’s still plenty of time to get down here. Late reg…","content":"Cards are in the air for the Friday Night Turbo at the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack at the Canad Inns in Grand Forks! We’re kicking things off strong with 5 tables already going, and there’s still plenty of time to get down here. Late registration remains open until 9 PM. Last year’s Friday Night Turbo champion: Joel Klipping – $1,500 Friday Night Turbo Details $100 buy-in – 15,000 starting chips Starts at 6 PM 20-minute blinds Late registration until 9 PM $100 rebuys for 15,000 chips $100 add-on for 15,000 chips until close of registration Max buy-in: $300 Suggested dealer appreciation: $20 Tips are appreciated, but not required Come out, shuffle up, and see who runs deep in Grand Forks tonight! DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-03-13 19:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"651233183_1595244512602621_8432823892227840256_n-GJW9DuMV.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/651233183_1595244512602621_8432823892227840256_n-GJW9DuMV.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":336,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (412, 'dakota-poker-tour-is-in-grand-forks', 'Dakota Poker Tour is in Grand Forks', 'The Dakota Poker Tour has made its way to the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND for the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend! Join us for two great days of poker action and support a great cause. Last time we were here, the winners walked away…', '2026-03-13 16:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/650535334_1594158749377864_936456110948628482_n-5C99VGDa.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/650535334_1594158749377864_936456110948628482_n-5C99VGDa.jpg', null, '{"id":412,"title":"Dakota Poker Tour is in Grand Forks","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-is-in-grand-forks","excerpt":"The Dakota Poker Tour has made its way to the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND for the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend! Join us for two great days of poker action and support a great cause. Last time we were here, the winners walked away…","content":"The Dakota Poker Tour has made its way to the Canad Inn in Grand Forks, ND for the L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack weekend! Join us for two great days of poker action and support a great cause. Last time we were here, the winners walked away with some serious cash: Friday Night Turbo Champion – Joel Klipping – $1,500 Saturday Monster Stack Champion – Sara Weishaar – $6,000 Who’s going to be the next champion in Grand Forks? Friday Night Turbo $100 Buy-in – 15,000 starting chips Starts at 6 PM | 20-minute blinds Late registration until 9 PM $100 Rebuys for 15,000 chips $100 Add-on for 15,000 chips (until close of registration) Max buy-in $300 Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated but not required) Saturday – L.I.S.T.E.N. INC Monster Stack NEW START TIME: 11 AM $300 Buy-in One-Day Monster Stack Event 100,000 starting chips | 30-minute levels Late registration available until 6 PM after the dinner break Suggested dealer appreciation $20 (tips appreciated but not required) Come out, shuffle up, and see who runs deep in Grand Forks! DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour Who’s making the trip to Grand Forks this weekend?","publishedAt":"2026-03-13 16:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"650535334_1594158749377864_936456110948628482_n-5C99VGDa.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/650535334_1594158749377864_936456110948628482_n-5C99VGDa.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":336,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-l-i-s-t-e-n-inc-monster-stack-friday-night-turbo-03-13-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (409, 'congratulations-ron-james-the-hole-in-one-champion', 'Congratulations Ron James the Hole in One Champion', 'Congratulations to Ron James of Mapleton, North Dakota, your Hole In One Champion! Ron outlasted a field of 93 players to take home $7,000 in cash after a great day of poker and competition. A huge thank you to the Angry Beaver Lodge in Oak…', '2026-03-01 01:30:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5722-aKZEzaoh.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5722-aKZEzaoh.jpg', null, '{"id":409,"title":"Congratulations Ron James the Hole in One Champion","alias":"congratulations-ron-james-the-hole-in-one-champion","excerpt":"Congratulations to Ron James of Mapleton, North Dakota, your Hole In One Champion! Ron outlasted a field of 93 players to take home $7,000 in cash after a great day of poker and competition. A huge thank you to the Angry Beaver Lodge in Oak…","content":"Congratulations to Ron James of Mapleton, North Dakota, your Hole In One Champion! Ron outlasted a field of 93 players to take home $7,000 in cash after a great day of poker and competition. A huge thank you to the Angry Beaver Lodge in Oakes, North Dakota for hosting another outstanding event. We also extend our appreciation to the Hole In One Foundation for generously taking only the state minimum and returning the maximum prize pool back to the players. Your continued support of both the community and the poker players does not go unnoticed. It was great seeing so many familiar faces and welcoming new players to the felt. Competitors traveled from across North Dakota, Minnesota, and South Dakota to support this event and the Hole In One mission. We’ll see everyone at our next stop March 13–14 for the L.I.S.T.E.N. Inc Monster Stack in Grand Forks, ND. Final Payouts: 1st – $7,000 Ron James – Mapleton, ND 2nd – $4,400 Lester Hauglid – Detroit Lakes, ND 3rd – $3,200 Cordell Schroeder – Carrington, ND 4th – $2,100 Stakovic Zlatko – Oakes, ND 5th – $1,700 Kristine McFarland – Gwinner, ND 6th – $1,300 Carin Kassa – Wahpeton, ND 7th – $1,100 Roger McLaen – Forman, ND 8th – $800 Don Eagen – Perham, MN 9th – $650 Robin Green – Groton, SD 10th – $550 Leroy Turner – Wolverton, MN 11th – $550 Matt Johnson – Fargo, ND 12th – $550 Serhill Hrysko – Moorhead, MN Stay connected with Dakota Poker Tour: DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour Thank you again to everyone who came out and supported a great cause. See you in Grand Forks! ♠️","publishedAt":"2026-03-01 01:30:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5722-aKZEzaoh.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5722-aKZEzaoh.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":335,"name":"Main Event","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (408, 'final-table-oakes-nd', 'Final Table Oakes ND', 'After a full day of great poker and tough competition, congratulations to your official Final Table: Don Eagen Ron James Roger McLean Kristine McFarland Robin Green Carin Kassa Cordell Schroeder Stankovic Zlatko Lester Hauglid Outlasting a…', '2026-02-28 22:45:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5719-ZFrP5JUV.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5719-ZFrP5JUV.jpg', null, '{"id":408,"title":"Final Table Oakes ND","alias":"final-table-oakes-nd","excerpt":"After a full day of great poker and tough competition, congratulations to your official Final Table: Don Eagen Ron James Roger McLean Kristine McFarland Robin Green Carin Kassa Cordell Schroeder Stankovic Zlatko Lester Hauglid Outlasting a…","content":"After a full day of great poker and tough competition, congratulations to your official Final Table: Don Eagen Ron James Roger McLean Kristine McFarland Robin Green Carin Kassa Cordell Schroeder Stankovic Zlatko Lester Hauglid Outlasting a strong field and earning a seat at the final table is something to be proud of. Thank you all for bringing the energy, the competition, and for supporting an event that gives back to our local community. A special thank you to all the familiar faces who continue to show up and support the Hole In One Foundation year after year. And to all the new faces — we hope to see you again soon! We truly appreciate the players who traveled from near and far, from Minnesota, South Dakota, and across North Dakota to be part of this event. We appreciate each and every one of you. Oakes showed up in a big way. ♠️🔥 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-28 22:45:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5719-ZFrP5JUV.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5719-ZFrP5JUV.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":335,"name":"Main Event","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (407, 'oakes-delivers-24k-prize-pool-and-7-000-to-the-champion', 'Oakes Delivers: $24K Prize Pool and $7,000 to the Champion', 'Huge thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and The Hole in One Foundation today in Oakes! Registration officially closed with 93 players, generating an incredible $24,000 prize pool. 🙌 Tonight’s champion is tak…', '2026-02-28 18:00:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5677-U140nHsH.png', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5677-U140nHsH.png', null, '{"id":407,"title":"Oakes Delivers: $24K Prize Pool and $7,000 to the Champion","alias":"oakes-delivers-24k-prize-pool-and-7-000-to-the-champion","excerpt":"Huge thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and The Hole in One Foundation today in Oakes! Registration officially closed with 93 players, generating an incredible $24,000 prize pool. 🙌 Tonight’s champion is tak…","content":"Huge thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and The Hole in One Foundation today in Oakes! Registration officially closed with 93 players, generating an incredible $24,000 prize pool. 🙌 Tonight’s champion is taking home $7,000, with the top 12 players all earning cash. What a day! As tradition holds, the Hole in One Foundation kept the state minimum 10%, giving the maximum payout back to the players — and that’s something we’re proud to be part of every time. The Hole in One Foundation is a Christian-based organization that gives back directly to our local community — helping friends, families, and neighbors facing financial hardship after major life-changing events. Funds are raised through poker, charitable gaming, and their annual golf scramble, and today you all helped make a difference. ❤️ Thank you for showing up, competing hard, and supporting something bigger than the game. Stay connected with DPT: DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour We’ll see you at the next stop. ♠️🔥","publishedAt":"2026-02-28 18:00:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5677-U140nHsH.png","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5677-U140nHsH.png","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":335,"name":"Main Event","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (406, 'poker-players-showing-up-in-oakes', 'Poker Players Showing up in Oakes', 'Poker players… where are you?! 👀 We’re already 8 tables strong and players are STILL entering here in Oakes! Don’t miss your shot — late registration is open until the 5PM dinner break. Last year’s champion walked away with $7,000 💰 Who’s m…', '2026-02-28 14:40:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/641636097_1584189320374807_8541594968132913524_n-wgHglL1W.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/641636097_1584189320374807_8541594968132913524_n-wgHglL1W.jpg', null, '{"id":406,"title":"Poker Players Showing up in Oakes","alias":"poker-players-showing-up-in-oakes","excerpt":"Poker players… where are you?! 👀 We’re already 8 tables strong and players are STILL entering here in Oakes! Don’t miss your shot — late registration is open until the 5PM dinner break. Last year’s champion walked away with $7,000 💰 Who’s m…","content":"Poker players… where are you?! 👀 We’re already 8 tables strong and players are STILL entering here in Oakes! Don’t miss your shot — late registration is open until the 5PM dinner break. Last year’s champion walked away with $7,000 💰 Who’s making a run at it today? 🔥 Rumor has it the chef whipped up pulled pork and cheddar mash for just $15 — come hungry and ready to play! Supporting a Great Cause ❤️ Today’s event benefits the Hole in One Foundation, a Christian-based organization that gives back directly to our local community — helping friends, families, and neighbors facing financial hardship after major life-changing events. They raise funds through poker, charitable gaming, and their annual golf scramble — and today they’re keeping the state minimum, giving the MAX prize pool back to the players! Come out and support an incredible cause, and our BFF Cody Slusher, who proudly serves on the board. ❤️ 🗓 Saturday 2/28/2026 – Single Day Event 🕚 Registration: 11AM 🕛 Cards in the Air: NOON 💰 $150 Buy-In – 20,000 Chips ⏱ 30-Minute Levels ➕ $50 Add-On = 10,000 Chips (up to 3 times – $300 max) ♻️ Add-ons available at start, during play, and for re-entry 🕔 Late Registration, Re-Entry & Add-Ons open until dinner break (~5PM) Suggested dealer appreciation: $20 (always appreciated, never required). Oakes… let’s GO! ♠️🔥","publishedAt":"2026-02-28 14:40:00","featured":false,"logo":"641636097_1584189320374807_8541594968132913524_n-wgHglL1W.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/641636097_1584189320374807_8541594968132913524_n-wgHglL1W.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":335,"name":"Main Event","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-hole-in-one-deepstack-main-event-02-28-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (405, 'dirty-dave-ledeman-is-the-buffalo-city-showdown-champion', '🏆 “Dirty” Dave Ledeman is the Buffalo City Showdown Champion', '🏆 “Dirty” Dave Ledeman of Dickinson, ND is your Buffalo City Showdown Champion! 🏆 The final three players — Dave, Tom, and Tim agreed to a deal to split the remaining prize pool, capping off an exciting day of poker. The Dakota Poker Tour d…', '2026-02-08 00:19:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5282-MJvmuaCY.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5282-MJvmuaCY.jpg', null, '{"id":405,"title":"🏆 “Dirty” Dave Ledeman is the Buffalo City Showdown Champion","alias":"dirty-dave-ledeman-is-the-buffalo-city-showdown-champion","excerpt":"🏆 “Dirty” Dave Ledeman of Dickinson, ND is your Buffalo City Showdown Champion! 🏆 The final three players — Dave, Tom, and Tim agreed to a deal to split the remaining prize pool, capping off an exciting day of poker. The Dakota Poker Tour d…","content":"🏆 “Dirty” Dave Ledeman of Dickinson, ND is your Buffalo City Showdown Champion! 🏆 The final three players — Dave, Tom, and Tim agreed to a deal to split the remaining prize pool, capping off an exciting day of poker. The Dakota Poker Tour dealers would also like to extend a huge thank-you to all of the players for their extra generosity — it truly means a lot. Thank you to everyone who came out to support Progress Enterprise, our host The Buff Bar, and their incredible staff for taking such great care of the players all day long. A special thank-you to the UJ Women’s D2 Hockey team for providing an excellent lunch of ￼ Knoephla soup and deer sausage — nothing but compliments all around! Extra thanks to Missy and Tom for all of the behind-the-scenes work that helped make this a great event for both players and staff. 📅 Next Stop: February 28th — Hole in One Tournament 📍 Oakes, North Dakota We’ll see everyone there! ♠️🎉 1st $3400 “Dirty” Dave Ledemam Dickinson ND 2nd $3400 Timothy Kutz Jamestown ND 3rd $3400Tom Soulis Jamestown ND 4th $1800 Larry Loose Jamestown ND 5th $1400 Niles Short Minnewaukan ND 6th $1200 Wade Schlecht StreeterND 7th $900 Mark Britton Mapleton ND 8th $700 Jackson Skjerseth Moorhead MN 9th Bubble - Basim Habib Moorhead MN 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-08 00:19:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5282-MJvmuaCY.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5282-MJvmuaCY.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":334,"name":"Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (404, 'final-table-at-the-buffalo-city-showdown', 'Final Table at the Buffalo City Showdown', '🎉 Congratulations to the Final Table at the Buffalo City Showdown! 🎉 An incredible 61 players came out today to compete, generating a $16,000 prize pool with $4,800 going to first place! Thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dak…', '2026-02-07 21:03:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5277-gHU8kI3d.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5277-gHU8kI3d.jpg', null, '{"id":404,"title":"Final Table at the Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"final-table-at-the-buffalo-city-showdown","excerpt":"🎉 Congratulations to the Final Table at the Buffalo City Showdown! 🎉 An incredible 61 players came out today to compete, generating a $16,000 prize pool with $4,800 going to first place! Thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dak…","content":"🎉 Congratulations to the Final Table at the Buffalo City Showdown! 🎉 An incredible 61 players came out today to compete, generating a $16,000 prize pool with $4,800 going to first place! Thank you to everyone who came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and Progress Enterprises — we truly appreciate each and every one of you. A special thank you to The Buff Bar for hosting and taking great care of our players, and to Progress Enterprises for generously keeping only the state-minimum 10%, ensuring maximum payouts back to the players. ♠️ Final Table Payouts: 1st – $4,800 2nd – $3,000 3rd – $2,400 4th – $1,800 5th – $1,400 6th – $1,200 7th – $900 8th – $700 Great poker, great atmosphere, and another fantastic event in the books! ♠️ 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-07 21:03:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5277-gHU8kI3d.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5277-gHU8kI3d.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":334,"name":"Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (403, 'down-to-35-players-at-the-buffalo-city-showdown', 'Down to 35 Players at the Buffalo City Showdown', 'Thank you to everyone who came out today for the Buffalo City Showdown, supporting Progress entrprise and the Dakota Poker Tour. We officially closed registration with 61 players, generating a $16,200 prize pool — an outstanding showing! A…', '2026-02-07 17:48:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_3343-ObrssFBD.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_3343-ObrssFBD.jpg', null, '{"id":403,"title":"Down to 35 Players at the Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"down-to-35-players-at-the-buffalo-city-showdown","excerpt":"Thank you to everyone who came out today for the Buffalo City Showdown, supporting Progress entrprise and the Dakota Poker Tour. We officially closed registration with 61 players, generating a $16,200 prize pool — an outstanding showing! A…","content":"Thank you to everyone who came out today for the Buffalo City Showdown, supporting Progress entrprise and the Dakota Poker Tour. We officially closed registration with 61 players, generating a $16,200 prize pool — an outstanding showing! A huge thank you to UJ Women’s D2 Hockey for providing delicious Nela soup and deer sausage for lunch today — our players truly appreciated it. Thank you to the incredible staff at The Buff Bar for keeping everyone hydrated and taken care of, and a special shoutout to Missy for all the hard work behind the scenes. With 38 players remaining, who will take home the $4800? Best of luck to all remaining players! ♠️🏆 💰 Payouts (Top 8 Paid): 1st – $4,800 2nd – $3,000 3rd – $2,400 4th – $1,800 5th – $1,400 6th – $1,200 7th – $900 8th – $700 Who’s going to make the final table and chase that $4,800 top prize? Let’s go! ♠️🏆 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-07 17:48:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_3343-ObrssFBD.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_3343-ObrssFBD.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":334,"name":"Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (402, 'cards-in-the-air-seats-still-open-at-the-buff-bar', 'Cards in the Air, Seats Still Open at The Buff Bar', '🔥 7 Tables… WHAT?! 🔥 Jamestown is showing up in a big way! We’re now at 7 tables and still growing — with 2 more hours of late registration open until 5:00 PM. Come on down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown , grab some lunch, and jump into the a…', '2026-02-07 14:44:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5250-HWOadYor.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5250-HWOadYor.jpg', null, '{"id":402,"title":"Cards in the Air, Seats Still Open at The Buff Bar","alias":"cards-in-the-air-seats-still-open-at-the-buff-bar","excerpt":"🔥 7 Tables… WHAT?! 🔥 Jamestown is showing up in a big way! We’re now at 7 tables and still growing — with 2 more hours of late registration open until 5:00 PM. Come on down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown , grab some lunch, and jump into the a…","content":"🔥 7 Tables… WHAT?! 🔥 Jamestown is showing up in a big way! We’re now at 7 tables and still growing — with 2 more hours of late registration open until 5:00 PM. Come on down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown , grab some lunch, and jump into the action! 🍲 The knephla soup and deer sausage smell absolutely delicious, so come enjoy some great food and even better poker. 💰 First place is shaping up to be OVER $4,000 CASH! Plenty of cards left to be dealt — don’t miss your shot! ♠️🃏","publishedAt":"2026-02-07 14:44:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5250-HWOadYor.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5250-HWOadYor.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":334,"name":"Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (401, 'poker-players-jamestown-it-s-go-time', '♠️ Poker Players — Jamestown, It’s Go Time! ♠️', 'Get down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown, four tables are already starting strong with plenty of room to grow! Tournament Details • Registration starts at 11:00 AM • Cards in the air at 12:00 PM • $150 buy-in for 20,000 chips • For every addit…', '2026-02-07 13:53:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/buff126-Bp0IbZjt.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/buff126-Bp0IbZjt.jpg', null, '{"id":401,"title":"♠️ Poker Players — Jamestown, It’s Go Time! ♠️","alias":"poker-players-jamestown-it-s-go-time","excerpt":"Get down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown, four tables are already starting strong with plenty of room to grow! Tournament Details • Registration starts at 11:00 AM • Cards in the air at 12:00 PM • $150 buy-in for 20,000 chips • For every addit…","content":"Get down to The Buff Bar in Jamestown, four tables are already starting strong with plenty of room to grow! Tournament Details • Registration starts at 11:00 AM • Cards in the air at 12:00 PM • $150 buy-in for 20,000 chips • For every additional $50, receive 10,000 more chips • $300 max buy-in for 50,000 chips • 30-minute blind levels • Late registration open until 5:00 PM Come out and support Progress Enterprise and the Dakota Poker Tour. ✅ Charity Bonus: Progress Enterprise is keeping only the state-minimum 10%, ensuring maximum payout back to our players! 🍲 Dinner Break Bonus! The Buff Bar has generously provided delicious knephla soup and deer sausage for all tournament players — thank you for taking such great care of our field! Grab your seat, shuffle up, and let’s make it a great day of poker! 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-07 13:53:00","featured":false,"logo":"buff126-Bp0IbZjt.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/buff126-Bp0IbZjt.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":334,"name":"Buffalo City Showdown","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-the-buffalo-city-showdown-buffalo-city-showdown-02-07-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (399, 'john-christiansen-wins-the-dead-money-open', '🏆 John Christiansen Wins the Dead Money Open', '🎉 Congratulations to our Dead Money Open Champion! 🎉 Congratulations to John Christiansen of Castleton, North Dakota, who battled through an impressive field of 85 players to take down the Dead Money Open and walk away with $6,500! 💰♠️ The…', '2026-02-01 01:26:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5109-y9OdIsM8.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5109-y9OdIsM8.jpg', null, '{"id":399,"title":"🏆 John Christiansen Wins the Dead Money Open","alias":"john-christiansen-wins-the-dead-money-open","excerpt":"🎉 Congratulations to our Dead Money Open Champion! 🎉 Congratulations to John Christiansen of Castleton, North Dakota, who battled through an impressive field of 85 players to take down the Dead Money Open and walk away with $6,500! 💰♠️ The…","content":"🎉 Congratulations to our Dead Money Open Champion! 🎉 Congratulations to John Christiansen of Castleton, North Dakota, who battled through an impressive field of 85 players to take down the Dead Money Open and walk away with $6,500! 💰♠️ The tournament generated a prize pool of over $22,000, thanks to an amazing turnout and incredible support for the Dakota Poker Tour and West Fargo Hockey. Thank you to West Fargo Hockey for their generosity in taking only the state-minimum 10%, ensuring maximum payouts back to the players, we truly appreciate your support of the poker community. We also want to thank our host, the M&J Saloon, and a special shoutout to Dee and her entire staff for taking such great care of our players all day long. And of course, thank you to our hardworking dealers — we couldn’t do this without you! 🏆 Final Table Payouts 1st – $6,500 – John Christiansen (Castleton, ND) 2nd – $4,100 – Basim Habib (Moorhead, MN) 3rd – $3,000 – Vu Truong (TX) 4th – $2,100 – Ryan Belen 5th – $1,640 – Anthony Sinnen (Moorhead, MN) 6th – $1,400 – Mike Schultz (Grand Forks, ND) 7th – $1,200 – Christopher Franck (Fargo, ND) 8th – $900 – Christopher Pierce (Fargo, ND) 9th – $700 – Serhii Hryshko (Moorhead, MN) 10th – $600 – Cash Mitchell (Fargo, ND) We’ll see everybody next Saturday, February 7, for the Buffalo City Showdown at The Buff Bar in Jamestown, North Dakota! ♠️🔥 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-02-01 01:26:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5109-y9OdIsM8.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5109-y9OdIsM8.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":333,"name":"Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (398, 'dead-money-open-generates-over-22-000-prize-pool', 'Dead Money Open Generates Over $22,000 Prize Pool', 'Registration has officially closed at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo, North Dakota. An incredible 85 players came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and West Fargo Hockey, generating a prize pool of over $22,000. West…', '2026-01-31 18:55:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/dead-money234-z0t03Hbe.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/dead-money234-z0t03Hbe.jpg', null, '{"id":398,"title":"Dead Money Open Generates Over $22,000 Prize Pool","alias":"dead-money-open-generates-over-22-000-prize-pool","excerpt":"Registration has officially closed at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo, North Dakota. An incredible 85 players came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and West Fargo Hockey, generating a prize pool of over $22,000. West…","content":"Registration has officially closed at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo, North Dakota. An incredible 85 players came out to support the Dakota Poker Tour and West Fargo Hockey, generating a prize pool of over $22,000. West Fargo Hockey wanted to truly give back to the players, withholding only 10%, resulting in a maximum payout returned to the field — thank you for that generosity! Payouts: 1st – $6,500 2nd – $4,100 3rd – $3,000 4th – $2,100 5th – $1,640 6th – $1,400 7th – $1,200 8th – $900 9th – $700 10th – $600 A huge thank you to Dee and the entire staff at the M&J Saloon for making our players feel welcome and taking care of everything we needed — we truly appreciate you. And of course, thank you to all of our dealers who came out, worked tirelessly, and gave it their all to help put on another fantastic tournament. We couldn’t do this without you. 📊 DPT Leaderboard: dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard 📅 DPT Calendar: dakotapokertour.com/calendar 🎥 DPT YouTube Channel: youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-01-31 18:55:00","featured":false,"logo":"dead-money234-z0t03Hbe.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/dead-money234-z0t03Hbe.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":333,"name":"Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (397, 'dead-money-open-kicks-off-strong-at-m-j-saloon-in-west-farg', 'Dead Money Open Kicks Off Strong at M&J Saloon in West Farg', 'We are off to a strong start at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo! We currently have six full tables and room to grow, so get yourself down here — it’s shaping up to be a great turnout. Last year’s winner took home over $6…', '2026-01-31 12:38:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5077-ScS4RWyE.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5077-ScS4RWyE.jpg', null, '{"id":397,"title":"Dead Money Open Kicks Off Strong at M&J Saloon in West Farg","alias":"dead-money-open-kicks-off-strong-at-m-j-saloon-in-west-farg","excerpt":"We are off to a strong start at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo! We currently have six full tables and room to grow, so get yourself down here — it’s shaping up to be a great turnout. Last year’s winner took home over $6…","content":"We are off to a strong start at the Dead Money Open at the M&J Saloon in West Fargo! We currently have six full tables and room to grow, so get yourself down here — it’s shaping up to be a great turnout. Last year’s winner took home over $6,000. Who’s going to make the run this time? Saturday Main Event – January 31, 2026 Registration opens at 11:00 AM Cards in the air at NOON Late registration until 5pm $150 buy-in gets you 20,000 chips with 30-minute blind levels $50 add-on for 10,000 additional chips (up to 3 times) Max buy-in of $300 for 50,000 chips Add-ons can be taken at any time, including at the start, and may be used for re-entries Late registration, re-entry, and add-ons remain open through the dinner break (approximately 5:00 PM) Suggested dealer appreciation is $20 — tips are appreciated but never required to play. Stay connected: DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-01-31 12:38:00","featured":false,"logo":"IMG_5077-ScS4RWyE.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5077-ScS4RWyE.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":333,"name":"Deep Stack","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-deep-stack-01-31-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (396, 'vu-truong-randall-smith-chop-the-friday-night-dead-money-turbo', 'Vu Truong & Randall Smith Chop the Friday Night Dead Money Turbo', 'Congratulations to Vu Truong and Randall Smith, who chopped first place in Friday night’s Dead Money Turbo each taking home $2050 Cash! A total of 52 players came out for the Friday Night Turbo, generating a $9,200 prize pool. Thank you to…', '2026-01-31 01:29:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-friday-night-turbo-01-30-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5066-K1j7L8NN.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/IMG_5066-K1j7L8NN.jpg', null, '{"id":396,"title":"Vu Truong & Randall Smith Chop the Friday Night Dead Money Turbo","alias":"vu-truong-randall-smith-chop-the-friday-night-dead-money-turbo","excerpt":"Congratulations to Vu Truong and Randall Smith, who chopped first place in Friday night’s Dead Money Turbo each taking home $2050 Cash! A total of 52 players came out for the Friday Night Turbo, generating a $9,200 prize pool. Thank you to…","content":"Congratulations to Vu Truong and Randall Smith, who chopped first place in Friday night’s Dead Money Turbo each taking home $2050 Cash! A total of 52 players came out for the Friday Night Turbo, generating a $9,200 prize pool. Thank you to everyone who showed up to support the Dakota Poker Tour and West Fargo Hockey, we truly appreciate it! Don’t forget, tomorrow’s Main Event kicks off with: • Registration starting at 11:00 AM • Cards in the air at 12:00 PM • $150 buy-in for 20,000 chips • For every additional $50, receive 10,000 more chips • $300 max buy-in for 50,000 chips • 30-minute blind levels Last year’s winner walked away with over $6,000. Will you be the next champion? Final Results – Friday Night Turbo 1st $2,050 Randall Smith – Mahnomen, MN 1st $2,050 Vu Truong – Fort Worth, TX 3rd $1,500 Lester Hauglid – Detroit Lakes, MN 4th $1,200 Keith Johnson – Moorhead, MN 5th – $950 Richard Lugert – Lidgerwood,ND 6th – $800 Mark Britton – Mapleton, ND 7th – $650 Ethan Hongess – West Fargo,ND See everyone tomorrow — let’s make it another big one! ♠️🔥","publishedAt":"2026-01-31 01:29:00","featured":true,"logo":"IMG_5066-K1j7L8NN.jpg","banner":null,"videoUrl":null,"imageUrl":"https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/IMG_5066-K1j7L8NN.jpg","bannerUrl":"","tournament":{"id":332,"name":"Friday Night Turbo","alias":"dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-friday-night-turbo-01-30-2026"}}'::jsonb),
  (395, 'whos-taking-home-2300', 'Whos taking home $2300', 'Registration is officially CLOSED at the Dead Money Open! We’ve got 52 players battling it out, generating a $9,200 prize pool, and tonight’s champion will be taking home $2,300. Who’s going to make the run and claim the victory? But we’re…', '2026-01-30 20:30:00', null, 'dakota-poker-tour-2026-dead-money-open-friday-night-turbo-01-30-2026', 'https://dakotapokertour.com/storage/article/thumb/624097261_1557797323014007_6731439949156077435_n-4ImSBlPS.jpg', '/media/dpt/article/624097261_1557797323014007_6731439949156077435_n-4ImSBlPS.jpg', null, '{"id":395,"title":"Whos taking home $2300","alias":"whos-taking-home-2300","excerpt":"Registration is officially CLOSED at the Dead Money Open! We’ve got 52 players battling it out, generating a $9,200 prize pool, and tonight’s champion will be taking home $2,300. Who’s going to make the run and claim the victory? But we’re…","content":"Registration is officially CLOSED at the Dead Money Open! We’ve got 52 players battling it out, generating a $9,200 prize pool, and tonight’s champion will be taking home $2,300. Who’s going to make the run and claim the victory? But we’re not done yet… Tomorrow is the Dead Money Open MAIN EVENT — and it’s going to be a good one. Saturday Main Event – January 31, 2026 Registration opens at 11:00am Cards in the air at NOON $150 buy-in – 20,000 chips 30-minute blind levels $50 add-on for 10,000 chips Up to 3 add-ons (max buy-in $300) Add-ons can be taken at any time, including at the start, and may be used for re-entry Late registration, re-entry, & add-ons open through the dinner break (approximately 5:00pm) Suggested dealer appreciation: $20 Tips are appreciated but never required to play Stay up to date with everything Dakota Poker Tour: DPT Leaderboard: https://dakotapokertour.com/leaderboard DPT Calendar: https://dakotapokertour.com/calendar DPT YouTube Channel: https://youtube.com/@dakotapokertour","publishedAt":"2026-01-30 20:30:0